

				bxt
				===
		

0.  Description.

	BXT is a box-drawing gadget.

1.  Operation.

	Choose a symbol and paste or cut a box.

2.  zûdefine cx

	cx = target context of box drawing gadget.
	z = `cx._BXT

3.  Variables

	_SYMBOLSû	vector of symbols to choose from
	_COLORSû	vector of colors
	_BOXEDû		(symbols drawn;indices into _BOX)
	_BOXû		n«4 array of y, x, #ys, #xs, indexed
			by _BOXED

	_CUTû		button; cut chosen symbol
	_OBJECTSû	slotfiller of symbols (choice)
	_OBJECTû	chosen object
	_PAGEû		20«35 page object (squarish)
	_COLOR_MAP:	20«35 colormap (squarish)

	_BXTû		outer layout

4.  Restrictions

	_PAGE controls rubber band callback
	_OBJECTS controls set callback
	_SYMBOLS controls set callback

5.  Example

		$load s
		$load bxt

		bûbxt.define `
		_SYMBOLSû`one `two `three `four `five `six `seven `eight
		show b

	First symbol is chosen.  Draw and redraw boxes.
	Select another symbol.  Draw and redraw boxes.
	etc.
	
	State of BXT is given by _BOXED and _BOX.




